Songwriter, producer and performer Sola Shittu aka Oshara has released a new single to express his aspirations and dreams of impacting lives with his music. Oshara, who had been doing music for 10 years, released the new single entitled ‘I wish’earlier in the week. The Ikere-Ekiti indigene launched himself into the music scene with his debut album, ‘Sent: The Commission’ in November 2011. He has since gone ahead to remain relevant with singles that include ‘All the best’, ‘Omo Ministreet’, ‘My Lagos Prayer’, ‘Proudly Ekiti (Mei shomo yahoo)’ and a host of others.   Lady Donli: Sacrifice I made for my music     Onos Morgan goes for gold in Italy     Yoruba films give more fame, Alesh   Oshara noted that his dexterity at what he does has seen him share same stage with prominent music acts like King Sunny Ade, Sinach, Nathaniel Bassey, Adekunle Gold, Idrish Abdulkareem, Alibaba, Gbenga Adeyinka, Alabi Pasuma, Sola Allyson, Adewale Ayuba and many others. The entertainer on his journey to self-discovery was also involved in several art expressions like acting, standup comedy, events anchor. Oshara is the CEO of Greenwave Productions, a full-fledged audiovisual production outfit.